<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-18T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-18T13:00:00-05:00" n="848" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d848">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C1199/305: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bucknell</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-18T13:00:00-05:00">November 18, 1937—1
                            p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>162. Your 364, November 9, 10 a.m.</p>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“For Thompson from Grady. Please attend December meeting of Economic
                            Committee as my substitute. Advise Stoppani. Letter follows.”</p>
                    </quote>
                    <p>The Department has no objection to Thompson serving in this capacity. You
                        should, in informing Stoppani of Thompson’s selection, state that Thompson,
                        at Grady’s request, will follow the proceedings of the December meeting and
                        report to Grady as his substitute.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>